If `rfl` doesn't work, we can try `native_decide`. This tactic will call Lean's native decision procedures to evaluate the statement. Since `#eval f 0` works, it is possible that `native_decide` can also compute the value correctly. 

However, `native_decide` is not always guaranteed to work, especially when dealing with partial functions. 

